festival.introText:
?WOODLAND DISCO FESTIVAL - Nottingham?
Saturday 8th July 2022
Newstead Abbey, Nottingham
12pm - 11pm
 
 
Join us for the return of Nottingham's most magical festival - Woodland Disco Festival! Submerged in the fairy tale setting of our new venue Newstead Abbey ~ 10 minutes from Nottingham City Centre ?
 
 

Expect a fully immersive festival as we enhance the natural surroundings of the Abbey grounds with our vibrant production & dazzling visuals - the perfect setting to showcase our internationally-acclaimed artists across 2 stages ?

 
Sign-up now and join us for a confetti soaked DISCO Extravaganza for 1 day only ?
 
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
 
Expect
* The biggest names in house & disco
* Huge festival level production
* Tons of Confetti & Disco Balls
* Fully Immersive Environments
* Delicious Street Food
* Incredible Heritage Venue with stunning woodland grounds
 
SIGN-UP NOW FOR ACCESS TO PRIORITY TICKETS
 
? Celebrating Love & Disco this Summer ?
 

? ?

reviews.title: Review of Woodland Disco Festival
reviews.body: Drinks were overpriced, water ran out to drink, water ran out to wash your hands.... apart from that, very good event!

reviews.title: Review of Woodland Disco Festival
reviews.body:
Absolutely amazing event!
Fantastic music, great vibes, awesome DJ sets.
The VIP benefits were a little disappointing 
Overall brilliant event xxx

reviews.title: Review of Woodland Disco Festival
reviews.body: It was disappointing that there was no coffee available. We have been to plenty of other festivals and a stall has been available to sell it. Also you could not hear the dj's in the VIP area because of the sets on the Maze stage.Hence only four stars.

reviews.title: Review of Woodland Disco Festival
reviews.body: we left, food was overpriced and small portions, no option for snacks, I.e crisps etc. lots of people left, we left at 5pm to go into town.

faqs.question: When is Woodland Disco Festival?
faqs.answer: Woodland Disco Festival takes place Saturday 8th July 2023.

faqs.question: How to get to Woodland disco festival?
faqs.answer:
By Train:

Closest train station is Nottingham railway station. This is approximately a 25 minute drive from Lime lane Woods.

By Car:

From the north:

M1 southbound coming off at junction 27 onto the A608.

From the south:

M1 northbound coming off at junction 26 onto the A610

faqs.question: is there camping available at Woodland disco festival?
Do you have disabled facilities?
faqs.answer: The Festival is on a flat field, with disabled toilets.

faqs.question: How much are Woodland Disco Festival tickets?
Where is Woodland Disco Festival?
faqs.answer:
Woodland Disco Festival is located at Lime Lane Woods, Nottingham.

Address:

Lime Lane,

Arnold,

Nottingham

NG5 8PW

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: Yes, there is a 4 month payment plan available currently. Please head to the ticket section for more details.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Does Woodland Disco Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: You will need to be 18 or Older. We operate a challenge-21 policy upon Entry and at All Bars, if you look younger than 21, bring ID.
